thread.title: Israel’s Capital of Olympic Skating? It’s Hackensack

author: Louise Radnofsky
title: Israel’s Capital of Olympic Skating? It’s Hackensack
text:
Almost every member of Israel’s figure-skating team at the Olympics lives in the same place, and it’s nowhere near the Dead Sea. It’s Hackensack, N.J.
The suburban New York town is home to skating’s most fledgling dynasty, where members use the local Ice House rink as a base and the federation president’s daughter as a coach. They don’t merely practice together. Many of them live together in a group house.
